children.title: ckeditor 3 ruins block tag display, adds breaks and tabs | CKEditor.com

annos.name: bookmarkProperties/description
annos.value: I searched but could not find this.ckeditor 3 nightly, using ff 3.5.The editor is destroying simple p tag formatting - and other blocks such as H1, div, etc. Surely it won't be released like this, will it?For example, every P tag has, just before the first word, an extra break and tab added, then in between p tags another extra break tag is added. If I go to source and clean this up, the editor just reinserts it again! Instead of saving what it should, or even the exact html I write:some textmore text.It is saving this: some text more text.This is destroying the display obviously. Compare old version no problem: http://www.fckeditor.net/nightly/fckedi ... fault.htmlNew version with problem: http://ckeditor.com/ckeditor/3.0rc/_sam ... class.html1) why does it insert this junk?2) how to prevent this?3) is there a "clean html" function as I've seen on other editors?As-is the editor cannot be used. I tried all sorts of config attempts to fix the problem above but nothing works. (Also quite a nightmare to get a refreshed version - refreshing normally often doesn't work.)I tried these two noted from 2.0:config.FormatSource = false ; config.FormatOutput = false ;Nothing. A search of the 3.0 core files doesn't turn up these terms anyway, so how to do it?Also:-how is the basic js file is different from the big main one? Result looks the same to me. -when I tried changing the language in config.js the editor didn't display at all. ??Ideas???Thanks for your help! Otherwise loving the editor but finding 3.0 can't quite be used yet.
